Julian K. SAYLOR, Appellant, v. F. G. ZERBST, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Atlanta, Georgia, Appellee. * No. 8606. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 12, 1937. *1016Julian Saylor, in pro. per. Lawrence S. Camp, U. S. Atty., and Harvey H. Tisinger and H. T. Nichols, Asst. U. S. Attys., all of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before FOSTER, SIBLEY, and HOLMES, Circuit Judges.

Writ of certiorari denied 58 S.Ct. 482, 82 L.Ed. —.

 PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
